To run execute 'bundle install' && 'bundle exec shotgun -p <port> config.ru'

Prerequisites:
ruby 1.8.7
rubygems 1.3.6
bundler 1.0.10

check ruby version & rubygems version, then:
gem install bundler

if you can't find bundler, make sure your GEM_HOME points to the correct location (usually ~/.gem)

To load up the preformatted data to collections venues & users, run:
* cd mongo-koulutus
* mongodump dump/3sq

or alternatively change to the ruby directory and just execute
* bundle install (if not done already)
* ruby load_data.rb

Links:
* MongoMapper - https://github.com/jnunemaker/mongomapper
* Sinatra - http://www.sinatrarb.com/
